chromosome scientists complete chromosomes
( agence france - presse , paris , 2 nd ) - a group of international scientists said they have completed the sequence of defining human chromosome 14 . this is related to many diseases on chromosomes , including those over 30 years old who may suffer from alzheimer 's disease .
this is the fourth pair of chromosome chromosome that has been completed so far . it is made up of more than 87 million pairs of oxygen dna ( dots ) .
the study published by the british nature science weekly shows that the sequence of chromosome is made up of 1,050 genes and genes .
the goal of genetic scientists is to provide diagnostic tools to discover defective genes and eventually provide treatment that can block these genes from causing obstacles .
international scientists led by the french gene research center gizenstpcom e - e said that the 14 th pair of chromosome genes and more than 60 species of chromosome genes are capable of immunity systems .
in previous studies on a number of diseases , chromosomes 14 pairs of chromosomes have been identified as chromosomes , which are characterized by mutually impaired leukemia , excessive perforations , certain types of vision and hearing damage , and initial alzheimer 's disease .
about 200,000 people in the united states are suffering from alzheimer 's disease , accounting for five percent of all americans suffering from alzheimer 's disease .
mankind has a total of 23 pairs of chromosome .
in the past three years , three pairs of chromosome , including 20 pairs , 21 pairs and 22 pairs , have been sorted out .
australia reopens embassy in manila
( agence france - presse , manila , 2 nd ) - australia reopened its embassy in the philippines today . the embassy was closed seven weeks ago because of so - called clear terrorist threat .
in a statement , the philippine foreign ministry said that australian ambassador to manila , david pears , telephoned philippine foreign minister mark vaile to announce the resumption of all operations at the embassy .
canada , like the european union and australia , closed their embassies on november 28 and reopened earlier this week .
hubble said that all the three ambassadors were satisfied with the philippines government 's enhanced security measures .
the closure of the embassy angered the philippine government , saying the so - called threat was exaggerated and the embassy closed down to damage the image of the philippines .
manila has removed police intelligence officials from their duties as he disclosed unconfirmed information on the terrorist threat of the australian and canadian embassies .
the eu office and the australian embassy were in the same building .
around the september 11 anniversary of the terrorist attacks in the united states , western diplomatic envoys in southeast asia were closed down one after another because they were threatened by the terrorist group , bin laden 's al qaeda and its local alliance .
australian fm says north korea 's bad behavior cannot get more aid
( afp , sydney , the 2nd ) australia has called on the international community to make joint efforts to make north korea believe that in contempt the nuclear nonproliferation agreement or other " abominable act , " it will not be able to obtain more aid or other concessions .
australia 's foreign minister downer said today that pyongyang 's decision to reactivate a disputed nuclear facility and expel un inspectors is obviously aimed at forcing international concessions in aid and trade .
australia is one of the few countries with diplomatic ties with north korea .
downer said : " we think what north korea wants to do is to gain concessions , aid and trade from other countries in the world , including the united states , in order to violate the agreed framework of the 1994 agreement . "
downer said in an interview with abc , " one point we have put forward to north korea is that the bad behavior will not receive any reward . "
downer pointed out : " expulsion of un monitoring personnel and reactivation of yongbyon nuclear facilities will stop the international community from providing support . "
" this will produce an adverse effect . we hope these diplomatic measures will be effective . "
" on the other hand , if we react too much , we will follow the plan of north korea .
we do n't want to do so . "
downer said australia was working closely with the united states and other major allies to compel north korea to cancel steps taken recently to revive its frozen nuclear programme .
downer said : " what we want to do is to ensure that international countermeasures are jointly taken . we do not want to adopt uncoordinated special countermeasures . "
