( agence france - presse , washington , 6th ) - u . s . president bush vowed that his soon - to - be - proposed economic revitalization plan would " work the working people " , not just the wealthy . he generally believes that the rich people would be able to gain the greatest benefits from the plan .
" tomorrow you will hear me that the us economy is one of the strongest in the world , " bush told a reporter in chicago who was looking forward to his official release of this program .
however , we believe that the us economy can grow stronger than it is now . "
president bush is expected to publish an economic revitalization program costing $ 600 - billion for 10 years , half of which will be used to absorb the cancellation of shareholders ' share profits and taxes , and urge the us congress to speed up the tax cut plan passed in 2001 .
whether this program can be smoothly promoted or not is regarded as a front - line battle in the us presidential election in 2004 , and the democratic party attacked bush 's blueprint as adding flowers to it and not as a burning plan put forward by the democratic party .
the eight - point proposal put forward by the democratic party mainly focused on an reward of 136 billion us dollars to boost consumption , with a total expenditure of 100 billion us dollars in the next 10 years .
house democratic leader pelosi said at a joint press conference with other opposition congressmen , " this is a fair , fast and sound plan .
bush led the white house in refuting the accusation that his plan was only aimed at rich people . bush said that his forthcoming economic revitalization plan focused on " boosting economic vitality and growth . "
bush said : " this plan will provide tax relief to the working population .
this plan is aware that people have more money to spend in order to create more jobs . "
