( agence france - presse , washington , 7th ) - u . s . said today that it is willing to hold talks with north korea , which is listed as an " axis of evil " . however , it will not offer any new reward to communist countries which are financially troubled to get them out of nuclear program .
us president bush 's administration is now facing double crises from iraq and north korea . officials of the bush administration and senior diplomats of japan and south korea issued a statement saying that this means that the us policy toward pyongyang " has taken a step forward . "
the statement said : " the us delegation explained that it is willing to talk with north korea about how it will perform its obligations to the international community .
however , the us delegation stressed that the united states would not offer any remuneration for north korea to fulfill its current obligations . "
us officials insisted , using diplomatic words , that they would not consider the process of negotiations until north korea abides by various agreements on banning nuclear weapons .
state department spokesman bao runshi said , " we are unwilling to pay a price again for the previous agreements . "
prior to this , the bush administration said that the united states would refuse to talk with the stalinist state until north korea gives up its nuclear programme based on uranium enrichment and plutonium .
