heavy snow kills more people in europe
( agence france - presse , vienna , 8th ) - heavy snow , low temperature in siberia and strong winds in various parts of europe have caused many deaths . meanwhile , highways , railways , air and sea traffic have been suspended .
last night 's temperature in moscow , the capital of russia , dropped to a cold level that even local people felt , bringing the death toll of six people to 239 this year , most of whom were vagrants and older people , including many drunk people .
three people in lithuania died last night , and many others had to cut their legs and fingers due to freezing injuries .
temperatures in the southern part of the country hit a record low in 16 years , dropping below minus 32.6 degrees celsius .
three illegal immigrants in slovakia also died of cold and fatigue on monday , and the temperature in the area dropped to minus 20 degrees celsius .
at the same time , civil defense units in all regions and outside europe have indicated that snowfall has paralyzed roads , train delays , and airports .
ice sheets and road accidents along the british railway have paralyzed traffic in some parts of the country , bringing heavy snow to the eastern part of the country .
in the czech republic , which suffered serious flooding last summer , the temperature in its border areas near slovakia dropped to minus 18 degrees celsius .
world study center lauds environmental revolution
( agence france - presse , washington , 9th ) - in its annual report on " world status , " the world environment research center , the environmental research organization , praised the arrival of the " environmental revolution " with an unusual optimism , pointing out that many countries are successfully curbing and resolving environmental , health and social problems .
" building a world that accords with our needs and at the same time allowing the next generation to enjoy a healthy society is no longer a daydream , " said fleischer , the head of the " caretaker world research center " on the 9th .
the current world situation report points out that one of the encouraging achievements is the use of renewable sources in germany , japan and spain , such as solar and wind vehicles , which is becoming more and more common .
fleischer said when talking about the success of pursuing a recycled energy strategy : " we are entering a new era . "
the report said that in the 1990 s , the global production of fenfluramine , the culprit of destroying the ozone layer , fell 81 percent .
in addition , the anti - polio movement initiated by the world health organization has reduced the number of cases of polio in the world from 350,000 in 1988 to 480 in 2001 .
the washington - based environmental research organization also commended local environmental achievements , such as the netherlands setting a 86 percent recovery rate for automobiles , denmark 's complete prohibition of the use of aluminium cans to replace recyclable glass bottles , and brazil 's use of recycled energy in 2001 .
the imf report said past achievements had brought hope for lifting the serious global threat , including malaria which claimed 7,000 lives a day and air , food and water pollution that caused 5,500 children to die unfortunately every day .
aol time warner chairman to resign in may
( agence france - presse , washington , 12th ) - aol time warner chairman kerry announced tonight that he will resign in may . he said that this move " is the best for the company . "
in explaining his decision , kerry said that he had decided to take steps to avoid shareholders ' criticism of him , " causing our capacity of cooperation like a team to be blocked , and focusing our attention entirely on our business . "
kerry , who monitors the merger of aol and time warner , which was agreed by the us federal council in january 2001 , will remain the director of aol and time warner 's board .
when the merger was announced in january 2000 , the value was us $ 155 billion , which was later endorsed by european policymakers .
kiss said in a statement : " as you have expected , this decision is very difficult for me personally . since i hope that in the next few years i will be the chairman of this big company , and as a co - author of the case , i have always believed that it is very important for me to leave the board of directors and assist me in handling matters . "
he stressed : " first , there is no need for the company to be uneasy at this critical moment . moreover , since some shareholders still gather disappointed at my operations after the merger with the company , i have decided that we should take action now to prevent our cooperation like a team from being obstructed and to focus on our business completely . "
aol time warner said its advertising and business sales are expected to decrease from 2.7 billion us dollars in 2001 to 1.5 billion us dollars in 2002 .
total sales would be us $ 8.8 billion to us $ 9 billion , and us $ 8.718 billion in the previous year .
the company estimated that the total sales volume of aol in 2003 would be almost the same as that of 2002 , while advertising and commercial sales would decrease by 40 to 50 percent .
north korea to withdraw from nuclear non - proliferation treaty
( agence france - presse , washington , 15th ) - u . s . and north korea 's stand has been upgraded from an " axis of evil " to an international crisis . efforts to spread global nuclear non - proliferation over the past decades will probably fall short of success .
pyongyang announced its withdrawal from the nuclear non - proliferation treaty on the 10 th of this month , dropping a standoff with washington .
analysts said the world 's efforts to curb nuclear proliferation are feared to have failed , and the treaty between india and pakistan , not signatory of the treaty , was seriously damaged when they entered the nuclear club in 1998 .
four days after pyongyang took the above actions , the five permanent members of the un security council have taken preventive diplomatic actions against the crisis .
russia said it would send a special envoy to pyongyang to propose ending the deadlock while china suggested hosting a compromise dialogue between the united states and north korea .
britain and france are discussing the crisis in london .
the international atomic energy agency has warned it may ask the security council to take action if pyongyang refuses to give up its nuclear program .
with regard to the actions of russia and china , many us observers feel that such talks may force moscow and beijing to decide whether or not to vote against north korea .
other countries that may have nuclear capability , such as iran and libya , will certainly keep a close watch on the development of the north korean crisis .
they will pay attention to north korea 's withdrawal from nuclear non - proliferation treaties and not being punished , or obtaining huge us funds to exchange for a halt to nuclear weapons .
" if north korea is considered capable of withdrawing from nuclear non - proliferation treaties , they may take the same action without paying a price , " said former state department arms control official ahern .
novsei of the institute of international economics believes that north korea may make a tactical mistake because its decision to withdraw from the non - proliferation treaty will make the international community more determined to resolve this issue .
japanese court rejects ex - chinese lackeys compensation lawsuit
( agence france - presse , tokyo , 15th ) - a japanese court today rejected a lawsuit of compensation of 142 - million yen ( 1.1 - million u . s . dollars ) . the lawsuit was lodged by six chinese . they were forced to work as lackeys at a nickel mine in japan during world war ii .
nannan , judge of the kyoto district court , said that although the government and the japanese metallurgical industry company jointly committed illegal acts in 1944 , he rejected the lawsuit based on the effect of the civil law requesting compensation for 20 years .
nmu said , " the defendant 's responsibility has been terminated . "
five former chinese slaves , including 72 - year - old liu zongen and a lackeys , sought unpaid wages , compensations , and apologies from the japanese government and the japanese metallurgical industry company .
these six people were slaves for one year in japan 's metallurgical industry . during this period , they were often beaten , and they had enough to eat and did not wear any warm clothing .
japan 's metallurgical industry argued that the company was unable to confront state policies , while the japanese government said it did not need to compensate the plaintiff according to the constitution at that time .
korean news agency , jiji press reported , after the court announced its verdict , liu zonggen said at a press conference : " this is a lack of humanitarian judgment . "
he said they will file an appeal .
liu zonggen said , " with the support of many japanese friends , i will fight to the end . "
the plaintiffs said the ruling " violated historical records " and demanded compensation and apology from the japanese government and japan 's metallurgical industry in order to resolve the problem .
this is the first time such a defense has been rejected in a war compensation lawsuit , kyodo said .
in 1944 , the japanese army arrested about 200 chinese and then sent them to the grand nickel mine in the city of kaesong as lackeys .
