japan needs to achieve real growth of 1.5% in 2006
( afp , tokyo ) nihon keizai shimbun said in a report today that the japanese government 's economic and fiscal advisory council has delayed the forecast period for japan 's economy to reach 1.5 percent in real terms for two years to 2006 .
the eec meeting also expected the annual total issue of treasury bonds to be as high as 40 trillion yen in the next five years because the budget deficit would be reduced longer than originally expected .
the economic outlook for the next five years is set to be finalized on june 20 , the report said .
the interim economic outlook , originally scheduled for early january last year , is being revised at the economic and financial advisory council meeting and is expected to be endorsed by the cabinet meeting by the end of this month .
the current edition of the interim economic outlook report and an experiment conducted by the cabinet are expected to achieve a real growth rate of 1.5% in 2004 and 2.7% in nominal terms in 2005 , the report said .
but the revised version of the report expected real growth of only 0.9 percent in 2004 , while nominal growth of 0.8 percentage points .
the revised version of the report is expected to achieve a real growth rate of 1.5% or above by the year 2006 , the report said .
the nominal growth rate of 2.5 percent or more will have to be recorded in the fiscal year 2007 , which will be postponed for two years from the original estimate .
the revised outlook report will also last for two years , the report said .
