( agence france - presse , sydney , 18th ) - australia 's forestry fire wreaked havoc today , destroying nearly 40 houses and threatening the homes of residents in the suburbs of canberra . with strong winds and rising temperature , the fire was expected to further expand .
australia officials said unconfirmed reports that one person had been killed and several people were missing in a blaze that extended to dozens of villages and towns around canberra and other areas directly under the australian capital , aux .
federal police officer brown said that police were trying to confirm that at least one person had died in the fire , but it is true that there were people missing .
the authorities of the capital 's direct jurisdiction declared a state of emergency today as a result of strong winds causing forest fires in the mountainous areas in northern , southern , and western canberra .
on the other hand , fire authorities said that the fire was approaching the most densely populated area and had already been urging the military to join the several thousand firefighters who put out the fire .
under the threat of the biggest forest fire in 50 years , people in mountain areas and towns in the new south wales province of new south wales and croatia have been evacuated in an emergency .
kpeberg , director of the township fire services department , said : " the situation is very grim . snow - capped areas may be facing the most serious threat in 50 years . more than 1,000 firefighters are fighting a continuous battle to retreat . they are unable to stop the fire from pouring 80,000 hectares of woodland into the province of new south wales . "
japanese emperor akihito goes on operations to smoothly remove the lung cancer - protector
( agence france - presse , tokyo , 18th ) - japanese emperor akihito underwent an operation today to remove the prophecies of cancer . doctors of the royal family said that the operation has proceeded smoothly and the cancer cells seem to have not spread to other organs .
" the operation was carried out smoothly and successfully , " kishizawa , medical chief of the imperial household agency , said at a press conference held at the teikoku university hospital in tokyo .
your majesty has awakened from numbness and talked to the princess of queen and chishino who accompanied him . "
he added , " judging from the appearance , we believe that ( cancer ) is not spreading . "
" doctors will carry out further tests to determine that cancer is limited only to the thyroid , " he said .
the operation was carried out by six doctors , which took three hours and 40 minutes to remove the entire memory of akihito .
the 69 - year - old akihito was in 1989 , the first time in history that the emperor has undergone an operation in a hospital outside the imperial hospital .
the doctor said that akihito will retire for about a month .
jinze said that during the operation , akihito did not have much bleeding and doctors only used their own blood for blood transfusion .
before the operation , the doctor had stored the blood of akihito in advance and the quantity was unknown .
chief cabinet secretary yasuo fukuda said that the government was gratified at the success of the emperor 's operation and hoped that he would recover at an early date .
a government official said that the 42 - year - old crown prince naruhito had taken responsibility for the constitutional duties of the emperor of japan not long after akihito was admitted to hospital .
this is the first time that the emperor has been transferred from hospital due to illness .
philippine forces gather to fight communist guerrillas
( agence france - presse , manila , 20th ) - philippine security forces are assembling to fight communist guerrillas ' massive attacks on the islands in southeast asia .
commander joseph prueher said today that the new people 's army is " attempting to build troops in certain areas , " including various provinces in the northern philippines , southern manila , and several central islands .
he also said , " they are stepping up attacks on areas they think there is a shortage of military forces , " or " attacking and harassment of troops in sparsely populated areas . "
other officials said the new people 's army had stepped up attacks on the so - called " soft " targets , such as telecommunications and power facilities .
last week , aibudan , head of national police , called on telecommunications companies to invest several hundred million dollars in security to prevent attacks by the new people 's army .
prueher said , " the armed forces have already deployed more troops in areas most likely to be threatened . "
joseph prueher said the new people 's army had reduced its personnel by 23 percent from 12,000 to 13,000 two years ago to about 9,000 .
among them , at least 5,000 are " armed regular armed forces " and around 6,000 are " armed forces " in early 2001 .
he said that the government troops beat them down in more than 400 villages of the new people 's army .
he said : " we are slowly but confirmed to win back the people 's confidence . "
the new people 's army suffered a serious military and political setback and forced it to return to the negotiation table with the philippine communist party at its source , the national security adviser said last week .
philippine president gloria arroyo stopped holding talks with the communist party in the mid - 2001 after rebels assassinated two philippine congressmen .
last year , the united states listed the new people 's army and the philippine communist party on its blacklist of " foreign terrorist organizations " .
washington , canada and many western european governments have also agreed to trace and stop the source of foreign financial resources of the rebels and freeze their overseas assets .
growth of cell phone users in mainland china to slow down
( agence france - presse , beijing , 21st ) - new cell phone users in mainland china are expected to reduce by 52 million this year .
last year , 61.9 million .
however , the beijing morning post quoted the prediction of the ministry of information industry as saying that this target may be underestimated .
in january last year , the ministry of information industry forecast that the number of new cell phone users would be 55 million , but the actual number would be 61.9 million .
at the end of last year , there were 206.6 million cell phone users in mainland china , an increase of 42.7 percent over the previous year .
beijing said that in july last year , mainland china became the world 's largest fixed - line and mobile phone market .
one year ago , cell phone users ranked first in the world .
meanwhile , information industry minister wu jichuan predicted that the declining investment in fixed assets in the postal and telecommunications sector would be halted this year , but the investment could remain the same .
last year , fixed assets investment in the postal and telecommunications industry decreased by 20 percent to 2210.6 billion yuan .
telecommunications investment accounted for 97% of the total investment .
wu jichuan predicted that the investment in fixed assets by the postal and telecommunications industry will reach 210 billion yuan this year , which is slightly lower than last year .
the ministry of information industry estimates that the number of new fixed - line telephone subscribers will be 33 million this year , down from 35.4 million last year .
at the end of last december , the number of fixed telephone subscribers in mainland china reached 211.4 million , an increase of 35 million over the previous year .
wu jichuan also promised to strengthen competition and speed up the establishment of a telecommunications control organ .
he said : " the optimization of telecommunications control has become the most important issue in the telecommunications industry .
we will speed up the drafting of telecommunications law , the revision of postal , judicial , and wireless management regulations . "
