german unemployment rises to five - year high in january
( agence france - presse , frankfurt , 5th ) - according to official data , the bad weather and long - term economic slump in winter have pushed germany 's unemployment rate to a new high in january this year , bringing another severe blow to german chancellor gerhard schroeder , who has only been reelected for 100 days .
in addition , germany , the biggest economy in the euro zone , is facing a gloomy economic situation because of the threat of a war in iraq .
the freezing of the german labor market seems to continue in the next few months .
the number of people looking for jobs in germany rose sharply to 4623,000 , or 11.1 percent of the german workforce , a five - year unemployment rate in january , the federal labour department said in its latest report .
in december last year , the total unemployed population reached 425,000 , and the unemployment rate was 10.1 percent .
for seasonal reasons , the number of unemployed in germany is usually on the rise in winter because of bad weather in general companies , especially the construction industry .
even if we calculate for this reason , those who applied for unemployment relief last month continued to increase .
the total number of unemployed people soared to 474,000 in january from 4212,000 in december , according to seasonally adjusted data released by the central bank in frankfurt .
meanwhile , the seasonally adjusted unemployment rate increased from 10.1 percent to 10.3 percent .
federal bureau of labor director geoffrey galster is due to the impact of the extraordinary winter weather and the economic difficulties .
full recovery expected for 2004 : oecd
( afp , singapore , 6 th ) the singapore economic review commission said that due to global geopolitical and economic tension , singapore 's economy is unlikely to recover completely by 2004 .
in its annual economic review report , the singapore economic review commission said , " the singapore economy has yet to completely recover from the recession since 2001 . there are too many instability in the region , the slow economic growth in europe , the forthcoming war in iraq , and the major challenges on the chinese mainland have cast a shadow on singapore 's near - term economic prospects . "
however , singapore 's economy this year still has a reasonable prospect of growth , but it could have to wait until 2004 if it wants a full recovery .
singapore 's economy is forecast to grow by two to five percent this year after 2.2 percent growth last year , down from an annual average of 7.3 percent since 1985 .
the economic review commission also suggested that the government postpone the plan of restoring the rates of employer provident fund contributions . two years later , it will consider increasing the rates of employer provident fund contributions so as to avoid increasing employers ' burdens , help reduce the unemployment rate , and disseminate effective information to foreign investors in the current difficult period .
