( afp report from washington d . c . ) the new york times quoted a us official as saying today that the white house is studying sanctions against pyongyang should it fail to abandon its nuclear weapons development action .
the sanctions will include measures to prevent north korea from sending weapons to north korea and cutting off north korean remittance abroad to north korea , the report said .
officials from the pentagon and the state department are drawing up detailed plans for imposing sanctions to enable the united states to respond at any time once north korea takes new measures to develop nuclear weapons , the report said .
the first step will be to urge the united nations security council to condemn north korea 's recent moves to develop nuclear weapons , including withdrawing from the nuclear non - proliferation treaty ( npt ) and re - opening its nuclear facility in yongbyon , the new york times reported . the timing may be in the next two weeks .
however , washington 's pacific allies are still opposed to the idea of imposing sanctions on north korea and the un security council is likely to focus on the iraq issue in the next few weeks .
at the same time , many us officials feared that north korea might seize the opportunity to push ahead with its arms production if the united states launches an attack on iraq , the new york times reported .
