study shows father gene may affect child birth time
( agence france - presse , paris , 28 th ) according to a danish research report published in the british medical weekly , which will publish saturday , father 's genes may affect the date of birth of children .
about five percent of pregnant women will produce late - production , that is , the time of pregnancy will reach 294 days .
at present , we know that this issue will cause health problems to mothers and children , but it is still a mystery as to why it is caused .
danish researchers tracked 43,000 births between 1980 and 1992 , with at least two children in each of the targeted mothers and having late production during their first pregnancy .
data for the previous two production periods were used for the purpose of analysis .
overall , nearly 20% of these women have the same experience during their first pregnancy .
however , when the first and second children were born out of different father , the ratio fell slightly to over 15% .
" there are already a lot of this , " said alison , head of the study 's report .
this means that if your partners ( the second child ) are the same , then you may have a longer pregnancy of 30 percent above the same partner . "
the report said : " women who change their partners during pregnancy can reduce the risk of repeated late - production .
we believe this is a new discovery .
and the result implies that the time of birth may be determined by the genes of my father . "
