xinhua news agency , berlin , january 4 , at least seven people have been killed recently in hurricane and floods in some european countries , including germany , belgium and the czech republic .
the water level of many rivers has risen , shipping for some major rivers has been forced to be suspended , and railway transportation has been affected as well .
in the city of munich , germany , the floods have swept across the embankment for four days , and the residents have no choice but to take water in their waist .
the town of vertem is expected to reach its highest water level in 80 years .
volunteers sent rubber boats to local residents for shopping .
government officials have also built platforms in the old city to facilitate people 's traveling .
cologne , a famous historical city , also avoided a robbery amid heavy rain .
shipping on the lavilla , 144 kilometers south of cologne , was forced to be suspended .
however , government officials said that the worst period has passed since the river continued to decline .
however , the flood situation remains serious in the small belgian town of ninova , with two people missing .
the belgian government has decided to recruit military personnel to build a dike in order to prevent further attacks on villages and roads .
