shanghai port overrides kaohsiung and becomes world 's fourth largest container port
xinhua news agency , shanghai , january 10 ( reporter feng yzhen ) according to information from the port industry , the container throughput completed by the shanghai port last year was 8.812 million teus , while the container throughput completed by taiwan 's kaohsiung port was about 8.991 million teus , and the shanghai port exceeded kaohsiung port , making it the world 's fourth largest container port .
last year , the global economy became warmer and the chinese economy continued to develop , injecting new vitality into the development of the shanghai port .
the container throughput of shanghai port in 2001 was 6.34 - million containers , which crossed two stages of 7 - million and 8 - million units last year , and container throughput reached 8.812 - million containers , an increase of 35.8% over the previous year . the total volume of cargo throughput reached 260 - million tons , up 19% from the previous year ; foreign trade export volume broke through 100 - million tons for the first time , increasing 22% over the previous year .
relying on its vast economic hinterland , the shanghai port has a huge network of direct shipping and has become the port with the largest number of air routes and maximum flight density .
currently , the shanghai port has flights in 12 air regions around the world and has trade relations with more than 40,000 ports in the world . it has flights to europe and north america everyday , and its flights go to the mediterranean sea , the persian gulf , and australia every week .
the number of flights is more than 1,300 each month .
this year , the container throughput of the shanghai port , which is speeding up the construction of the international shipping center , will exceed 9.5 million teus , striving to reach 10 million teus , and fulfilling the original target one year ahead of schedule .
