eu rules out trade in diamond against anti - monopoly
xinhua news agency , brussels , january 16 ( reporter tian fan ) the european commission announced on the 16th that the eu initially identified the world 's largest diamond supplier , durers , and russian diamond company , which signed a 4 - billion - euro diamond trade contract , violated the anti - monopoly law of the eu .
debilit , both in south africa and the united kingdom , controls 60% to 65% of the world 's rough diamonds , while the russian diamond company is the only russian diamond mining company , and is also the world 's second largest manufacturer of unprocessed diamonds .
under the five - year contract signed by the two companies , the russian diamond company has agreed to provide the company with half of its annual diamonds worth 800 million euros ( 800 million euros ) , and then the company will be responsible for pushing them into the market .
the european commission said in a statement that the contract would limit the free competition between russia and the world diamond market and enable the company to abuse its leading position to effectively control the quantity , quality , and even prices of diamonds in the world market .
according to the anti - monopoly law of the eu , these two companies can raise objections to the decision made by the eu commission within two months , and the eu commission will also continue its anti - monopoly investigation .
