xinhua news agency , tokyo , january 22 ( reporter : yue shaoyan ) - the central bank of japan decided at its meeting on the 22nd to maintain its current financial policy . the total amount of funds provided to the market remains at the level of 150 - 220 - trillion yen ( 1 us dollar equals 118 - billion japanese yen ) .
on the question of the demand of the government and the ruling party for " setting a target of moderate inflation , " the meeting held that it is necessary to adopt a prudent attitude .
the meeting held that although the economic outlook in japan is getting worse , the stock market and financial market have stabilized and there has been no major change in the economic situation . therefore , it was decided to maintain the existing financial policy .
on the issue that the government and the ruling party have asked the central bank to further relax its money supply and set an appropriate target for inflation , the central bank believes that japan 's financial market has sufficient funds .
if there is a shortage of funds in the financial market in the future , the central bank will increase the amount of capital investment according to the need .
