shenzhen lo wu customs severely cracks down on currency smuggling
xinhua news agency , shenzhen , january 25 ( li nanling ) - while ensuring civilized and highly efficient supervision and management , the luohu customs in shenzhen has also severely cracked down on currency smuggling through tourist inspection channels .
last year , the customs cracked a total of 1,023 monetary cases , involving a total value of more than 150 - million yuan . among these , 15 were individual cases involving more than 500,000 yuan ( excluding foreign exchange settlement cases ) .
as the country 's largest passenger inspection port , lo wu customs is charged with the task of supervising and controlling more than 250,000 passengers a day . if it is not strictly controlled , there may be a substantial outflow of money every day .
in the face of such a situation , we have always adopted strict supervisory measures , carried out thorough investigations , and strictly guarded against the outflow of money in our country .
at about 09:00 hours on 19 february last year , a middle - aged woman , who was carrying a baggage and walking fast , attracted the attention of customs officers .
after passing the luggage car , the customs officer found that there were suspicious objects inside the luggage compartment . he opened the luggage check and found that the boxes were actually tied up with three large black plastic bags amounting to hk $ 3 million .
this is the largest case of transmigration of passengers beyond the currency seized by the customs in the past two years .
in july and august of last year , foreign " underground banks " attempted to take advantage of the summer holiday at lo wu control point to smuggle a large amount of foreign currencies into and out of the country , using the opportunity of renovation and crowded personnel at the port .
the customs has attached great importance to this , laid stress on manpower deployment at the scene , and resolutely cracked down on the smuggling of foreign currencies by the " underground banks . "
from 2 july to 1 august , luohu customs cracked a total of four smuggling cases involving foreign currencies , involving a total value of over 14.66 million yuan .
