( international ) us personal consumer spending up 0.2 percent in 1998
xinhua news agency , washington , january 31 ( reporter wang zhenhua ) according to a report released by the us department of commerce on the 31 st , the growth rate for the whole year of 2001 was only the same as that of 2001 , despite a relatively rapid growth in personal consumption in the united states .
personal consumer spending rose by 0.9 percent in the last month , the biggest increase since july 1996 .
spending on durable goods rose 6.1 percent , while spending on non - durable goods and services increased only 0.2 percent .
this is a clear indication of the peak season for seasonal consumption in the united states .
in the last quarter of last year , personal consumer spending , which accounted for about two - thirds of the gross domestic product ( gdp ) , increased by only 1 percent , compared with 4.2 percent in the third quarter , the smallest increase since the first quarter of 1993 .
economic analysts believe that this is mainly because uncertain factors such as the united states ' possible war against iraq , a sharp fall in the stock market , and a weak job market have curbed consumer enthusiasm , and this has become the most important reason for the sharp slowdown of the us economy in the fourth quarter .
consumer spending in the united states increased by 4.5 percent last year , the same as in 2001 .
the report also showed that personal income in the united states increased by 0.4 percent in february last year .
personal income in the united states rose 3 percent last year , down from 3.3 percent in 2001 .
consumer spending , which is higher than income growth rate , declined from 4.5 percent in november to 4.1 percent at the end of last year .
