us construction spending up in december
xinhua news agency , washington , february 3 ( reporter he ying ) the us commerce department said in a report on the 3 rd that us construction spending in february last year was up 1.2% from january to november , after a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 858.3 billion us dollars .
housing construction increased at an annual rate of 434.6 billion dollars in the month , an increase of 2.9 percent over the january - november period .
analysts said low interest rates are an important factor in the strong growth of housing construction .
the u.s. federal reserve ( fed ) has kept short - term interest rates stable at 1.2 percent , the lowest in 41 years .
however , the commerce department reported that business construction spending in the month dropped by 1.9 percent from a seasonally adjusted 158.6 billion dollars in the same month last year .
analysts said the outlook for the u.s. economy is unstable , and businesses are unwilling to invest more in building factories and other facilities .
in addition , concern over terrorist attacks has also had an adverse impact on commercial construction . although bush signed the terrorist insurance act last november , it is not enough to dispel investors ' worries .
for all of last year , us housing construction spending fell to 0.4 percent from 2.7 percent in 2001 , the lowest level since 1991 .
