xinhua news agency , macao , february 10 ( reporter li jie ) according to information from the macao special administrative region ( sar ) government , macao 's fiscal budget for 2002 was carried out well , with a total surplus of 1.7 billion patacas ( about 13 percent of the annual budget ) .
according to sources , macao 's budget for 2002 was originally a deficit budget , with a revenue deficit of 8700 million yuan .
after balancing the surplus in 2001 , macao 's surplus was 300 million yuan , which is expected to be used to make up for the loss over the years .
however , the sar government is trying to increase revenue and reduce expenditure in the course of implementing the plan , which is about 10 percent higher than the estimated actual revenue and 8 percent less than the actual expenditure .
financial secretary ai wei - li said that the increase in macao 's budget for 2002 was mainly due to the successful opening up of the gambling and lottery industry , the telecommunications industry , and the recovery of the real estate industry .
statistics show that the amount of betting duty increased significantly in 2002 from 2001 , the number of subscribers in the telecommunications industry rose sharply , property market transactions became more active , and real estate transfer stamp duty alone increased by 30% .
( hong kong , macao and taiwan ) macao passes bill to avoid double taxation
xinhua news agency , macao , february 11 , the legislative council of the macao special administrative region ( sar ) on the 10 th passed a bill to empower the chief executive of the macao special administrative region ( sar ) to sign an avoidance of double taxation agreement with foreign countries .
the so - called " double taxation " refers to the fact that two or more tax jurisdictions collect the same or similar taxes on the same taxpayer , the same time and the same amount of duty payable .
the bill holds that in the event that macao is subject to double taxation , the chief executive has the right to adopt necessary measures until a district level agreement on the avoidance of double taxation is signed .
legislative council members responsible for examining this bill , entitled " the double taxation system in the international or regional double taxation situation , " said that at present the trend of global economic integration is becoming more and more obvious , and the taxation system must catch up as soon as possible ; otherwise , the flow of funds , commodities , and personnel will be restricted .
macao needs to sign agreements with other regions on avoiding double taxation , which is conducive to attracting foreign investment and also conducive to macao 's foreign investment , and is an important link in promoting macao 's economic development .
it is reported that macao and portugal have already signed a double taxation agreement , and the signing of the agreement is under discussion , and an agreement is expected to be reached by the middle of this year .
