( international ) study reveals overcoming obstacles to premature infant learning
xinhua news agency , washington , february 15 , premature infant suffering from underweight general intellectual development is vulnerable to learning obstacles .
researchers from yale university in the united states recently found that with the increase of age , this kind of educational barrier can be overcome .
research confirmed that the nerve system of premature infant suffering less than 1,500 grams could easily cause problems , among which up to 50 percent needed special assistants when attending school .
although many experiments before this showed that animals could recover from early brain injuries , there had never been any report about early infant suffering brain injuries .
according to the media here , researchers at yale university followed up and observed 300 premature babies . they conducted intelligence tests at their age three and a half years old , six years old , and eight years old , and found that the majority of them continuously improved their study ability with the passage of time .
the testing said that at the age of three , an early child classified as an " intellectual barrier " reached the normal level in language understanding and intelligence survey five years later .
however , 23 percent of infants still suffered from serious brain injuries due to cerebral bleeding , and the state of intellectual development has not changed .
researchers said that a key factor in the early birth intellectual development is the family environment .
intellectual property test results for children from 3 families and mothers who have received higher education are higher .
