( international ) chile , china sign mou on animal and plant hygiene
xinhua news agency , santiago , february 17 ( reporter hou yaohe ) china 's state administration of quality supervision , inspection and quarantine and the chilean ministry of agriculture signed here on the 17th a memorandum on the implementation of health and plant hygiene measures agreement .
according to the mou , china and chile will formulate quarantine requirements for imported and exported animals and plants , animal and plant products , and food products in accordance with the rules of the agreement , the standards formulated by the world organization for animal health , the international convention for the protection of plants , and the codex alimentarius commission .
the memorandum stipulates that the two sides should implement inspection and quarantine work on imported and exported animals and plants , animal and plants products and food in strict accordance with the protocol or the inspection and quarantine requirements agreed upon by the two countries , strengthen market access for animals , plants , and food on the scientific basis , and attach inspection and quarantine certificates to the export products .
the memorandum was signed by ge zhirong , deputy director of the state general administration of quality supervision , inspection and quarantine of china , and basra , acting chilean minister of agriculture .
