xinhua news agency , brussels , february 19 ( reporter feng jian ) the latest statistical report released by eu statistics bureau on the 19 th showed that due to the substantial decrease in imports , euro zone 's foreign trade realized a favorable balance of 102.3 billion euros in 2002 , more than double of that of the previous year .
the report showed that the euro zone 's trade surplus stood at 49.5 billion euros in 2001 .
the trade surplus was 6.1 billion euros last year .
the report attributed the sharp decline to the increase in the trade surplus .
according to statistics , compared with 2001 , the total imports of the euro zone and the eu as a whole decreased by 4 percent , while exports increased by 1 percent .
in the first 11 months of 2002 , imports from japan and the united states fell 12 percent and 11 percent respectively , while exports to japan and switzerland dropped 6 percent .
among eu member states , germany was the biggest trading partner , with a trade surplus of 117.9 billion euros while britain became the biggest trading partner among eu members with a deficit of 63.6 billion euros .
