xinhua news agency , shanghai , february 20 ( reporter wang hongyang ) - - the number of financial cases in the two provinces of zhejiang and fujian , which are located at the forefront of china 's financial and trade center and the forefront of financial reform and opening up , dropped 44.4% from the previous year , and the amount involved dropped 22.8% . the number of cases dropped to the lowest level in 13 years .
according to the latest news from the shanghai branch of the people 's bank of china , in recent years the financial sectors in various localities of shanghai , zhejiang , and fujian have comprehensively improved their systems to investigate , handle , and guard financial cases , effectively curbed the trend of a high incidence of financial law - breaking and discipline - violating cases , and brought about a favorable situation in which the number of cases , the amount of money involved , and the number of major and important cases involved , and the number of cases
statistics show that compared with the previous year , the number of financial cases involving the two provinces and one municipality decreased by 22.9 percent and 35.4 percent respectively in 1999 and 2000 ; the amount involved dropped by 41 percent and 11.2 percent , and the amount involved in the cases decreased by 35.4 percent in 2001 .
it has been learned that various localities in shanghai , zhejiang , and fujian have successively established a five - in - one case prevention system to " investigate , handle , reform , establish , and supervise " cases in line with the characteristics of the financial industry in their respective localities . at the same time , together with various functional departments , supervisory departments , and local judicial organs within banks , insurance companies , and securities companies , they have formed a socialized network for preventing financial cases .
( international ) eu stops importing beef from paraguay
xinhua news agency , buenos aires , february 20 ( reporter shen an ) the european union ( eu ) has decided to suspend imports of beef from paraguay due to the foot - and - mouth disease problem in paraguay , according to a report from paraguay agriculture ministry .
paraguay 's minister of agriculture , animal husbandry and animal husbandry , papargitani , announced that the eu made the above decision at a meeting on july 19 .
in early february , a report submitted by a inspection group of the european commission 's food and veterinary office after an inspection of paraguay was found to be inadequate in the control of foot - and - mouth disease . there were " serious problems " in the control of foot - and - mouth disease and the inspection system . it did not comply with eu requirements in areas such as health control , professional and technical standard , or export licensing system .
paraguay , which was the first case of foot - and - mouth disease in october last year , adopted quarantine and control measures with the help of other member countries of the southern common market .
paraguay exports about 60,000 tons of beef annually , mainly to brazil and chile .
these countries have stopped importing beef from paraguay .
the eu imported 567 tons of beef from paraguay from january to october last year .
( international ) austrian researchers find spellitus cells causing chronic pain
xinhua news agency , vienna , february 20 ( reporter lin chuan ) researchers at the university of vienna in austria found a group of nerve cells with a long memory . these cells will be slightly excited by the pain and take another step forward in searching for chronic illness .
the chronic pain patients are extremely sensitive to the pain and must eventually bear the pain in their daily lives .
however , people are almost totally unaware of the cause of the disease .
according to a report by the austrian news agency , a research team led by juergen sangchle , director of the nerve science department of the institute of the university of vienna , found that some spillings had not performed exceptionally well under normal conditions and would be excited after suffering from pain .
the pain was strongly stimulated , and the reaction was enhanced .
however , unlike other nerve cells , the cells of this group will become too sensitive to the stimulation of pain , even if they are only stimulated by insignificant pain .
researchers also found that there is a special channel in the polio cells , which will be opened when the cells are stimulated , and calcium plasma is flowing into the cells , thus further triggering chain reactions .
santol believes that the reason why those suffering from chronic pain were too sensitive to minor pain was that the nerve cells in the polio had a lasting memory and " traces of pain " were preserved .
he said that this discovery could lead people to look for ways to eliminate this memory .
china 's consumer prices up in january
xinhua news agency , beijing , february 21 ( reporter liu dongkai ) monthly report released by the state statistics bureau on the 21st shows that the overall level of chinese residents ' consumer prices in january rose 0.4 percent over the same month last year , the first rise in a row over the past 12 months .
according to the state statistical bureau , the main reason for the increase in the overall consumer price index was that the spring festival was held at the end of january this year , but the spring festival of february last year was different , so there was a definite comparison factor .
another reason is that the weather this year is cold compared with last year .
of the 31 provinces , municipalities , and autonomous regions surveyed in china , 22 residents ' consumer prices rose compared with the same period last year , and the remaining seven decreased compared with the same period last year .
statistics show that among all categories of consumer goods , the prices of seasonal consumer goods and services such as fresh vegetables , fresh fruits , and cultural entertainment rose , while the prices of grain , clothing , and consumer durable goods , which had a bearing on the long - term consumption trend , declined .
the rise in the prices of gasoline and diesel has led to a rise in liquefied petroleum gas prices and a further rise in housing prices .
chinese tv series on sexual education in primary and middle schools
xinhua news agency , haikou , february 21 ( zhang chuanxuan and liu wei ) china 's first " lecture on knowledge of sexual education in primary and middle schools " television series has been broadcast recently in haikou . the television series has evoked strong repercussions among teachers and students .
this series of sex education films published by the hainan province electronics and audio - video publishing house are divided into primary and middle school editions and senior middle school versions .
it introduces sex knowledge in an orderly way according to different age stages , including such special topics as qingchun , pregnancy , childbirth , aids protection , and sexual psychology , and uses vivid audio and visual paintings to answer questions raised by the children .
on the first broadcast held at the zhenfa school in hainan , more than 100 people on the verge of passing through seriously and quietly .
in the beginning , many girls only lowered their heads to read books and refused to raise their heads , but gradually viewed the pictures with ease .
lai ruixing , principal of the middle school , said the school needed such materials for sex education . this solved the embarrassment of the teachers choosing to talk and students secretly looking at .
the publication of this series of films has also been affirmed by relevant departments .
in november 2002 , a series of television series of " lectures on knowledge on sex education in primary and middle schools " won the 10th china population and culture award , which was presented by the state family planning commission and the china population and culture promotion association .
first chinese tourist delegation to malta to start tour
xinhua news agency , beijing , february 22 ( reporter qian chunxian ) it was learned on the 22 nd that the first chinese citizens traveling to egypt will leave here for malta on march 28 .
chinese tourists can make traveling across two continents in europe and africa within 10 days .
at that time , tourists can fly from beijing to cairo for five days on an egyptian airline flight and then fly to malta .
the entire 10 - day tour is expected to cost about 16,000 yuan .
malta is located in southern europe , close to italy .
the scenery of its blue sky and the warm atmosphere of the central sea have made it a famous tourist attraction in the world .
egypt is one of the four ancient civilizations in the world , and its long history has attracted tourists from all over the world .
malta became europe 's first chinese citizen to travel at its own expense in 2001 , and egypt became the first african citizen to target at its own expense in 2002 .
egyptian air formally opened its first direct flight from cairo to beijing in january this year .
the first delegation was jointly launched by the maltese national tourism administration , the egyptian tourism bureau , and the international travel agency .
( international ) blix calls for iraq to start destroying the " sammo " missile within a week
xinhua news agency , united nations , february 22 according to a report by the media here on the 22nd , hans blix , chairman of the un monitoring , verification and inspection commission ( unmovic ) , has issued an ultimatum to iraq demanding that iraq start destroying its " saad " missile within a week .
blix , spokesman for the unmovic said that blix had passed the ultimatum on the " destruction of sammo - 2 " missile and related equipment , asking iraq 's un permanent representative to the united nations mohammad kasi to begin destroying this prohibited weapon by 1 march .
a copy of the ultimatum has been submitted to the united nations security council .
experts concerned believe that this ultimatum makes iraqi president saddam faces a dilemma of either advancing or withdrawing .
destroying these missiles will make iraq lose important weapons for defending against an attack by the united states , and rejecting the demand of the iaea , which will give the united states and britain more excuses to take military actions against iraq .
blix and elbaradei , director general of the international atomic energy agency , said in their second report submitted to the security council on the 14 th that the firing range of the " saga " missiles has exceeded 150 km and violated the relevant resolutions of the security council .
( international ) georgian president stresses efforts to stop chechen illegal armed forces from entering pankki valley
xinhua news agency , moscow , february 24 ( reporter dong longjiang ) news from tbilisi : georgian president shevardnadze stressed in a speech on the georgian state radio station on the 24th that the primary task of georgia 's law enforcement department is to prevent and completely stop chechen illegal militants from sneaking into the panki valley .
shevardnadze said that in a special operation launched last autumn by georgia 's interior troops , police units , security departments , and defense ministry , foreign armed groups that sneaked into the panxi valley have been cleaned up and cleaned up . however , we cannot rule out the possibility that some illegal armed elements continue to hide themselves in the pankexi valley as refugees .
shevardnadze said that georgia 's law enforcement departments are capable of discovering these illegal militants .
at the same time , he also announced that georgia 's law enforcement departments will continue to carry out operations to eliminate illegal armed forces in the panxi valley in the near future .
in his speech , shevardnadze stressed the importance of cooperating with and exchanging intelligence with russia and the united states on this issue .
the panji - xixia valley is located in georgia and adjacent to the chechen region in russia .
russia holds that a large number of chechen illegal militants are hiding in the panxixia valley , accusing georgia of providing asylum to them .
last year , relations between russia and georgia were once tense because of the pankisi valley issue .
( international ) new york stock market falls again as us and britain put forward proposals to attack iraq
xinhua news agency , new york , february 24 , investors are worried that the three major stock indices on the new york stock exchange fell sharply on february 24 , setting a record fall since january 30 as the united states and britain insisted on submitting a new military attack on iraq to the un security council .
in addition , the latest us retail business report shows that retail sales in the united states in february do not allow for optimism , which has further undermined investors ' confidence .
the dow jones industrial average closed down 159.87 at 8,758.24 , down 2% . the technology heavy nasdaq composite index fell 26.64 points or 2% to 1,322.38 , and standard ; poor 's 500 index fell 15.59 points or 1.8% to 8,332.58 .
the russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 0.14 at 436.88 , but the american stock exchange index rose 0.43 at 436.43 .
advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5 - to - 2 margin on the new york stock exchange , with volume down to 15.3 billion shares from 17.01 billion in the previous session .
china red cross society raises donations to xinjiang disaster area
xinhua news agency , beijing , february 25 ( reporter wu jing ) the china red cross society opened a telephone donation account and a donation account on the 25th , appealing to people from all walks of life at home and abroad to extend their help to xinjiang compatriots who were hit by the earthquake on the 24th .
red cross donated telephone number : 010 - 6513 9999 ( 24 - hour shift )
account no : icbc east - south sub - division 02000010144132 - 52
the chinese red cross society has urgently transferred 250,000 yuan to the xinjiang disaster area after the earthquake on the 24 th and sent a relief team to the disaster area again on the 25 th .
an earthquake measuring 6.8 on the 24 th hit the baschu - jiashi prefecture in southern xinjiang .
by the early morning of the 25 th , the death toll had risen to 261 , seriously injuring 2,050 people and destroying 8,861 houses .
at present , the temperature in the disaster areas is about 2 degrees celsius below zero , and disaster victims are badly in need of food and clothing .
( international ) brazilian national risk index down
xinhua news agency , brasilia , february 27 ( reporter yang limin ) the brazilian national risk index fell 2.37% from the previous day to 1191 .
the index dropped below 1,200 points for the first time in eight months since the financial turmoil in june last year .
meanwhile , brazilian bonds traded on the international market rose 0.42 percent to 74 percent of the face value .
this was also the best record in eight months .
the national risk index is closely related to bond prices , the higher the index , and the lower the bond price .
last year , the brazilian national risk index exceeded 2,400 , and bond prices fell to 48 percent of the face value .
since the new government took office this year , brazil 's national risk index has continued to decline .
the report said that the price of the brazilian bonds is cheap and the rate of return is high , and the demand has increased sharply , which has led to a fall in the country 's risk index .
however , analysts pointed out that , although international investors are optimistic about brazilian bonds at present , if the us - iraq war breaks out , the national risk index is likely to rise again and bond prices fall again .
